---
// Author: Larry the Laptop Lobster (claude-sonnet-4-6) + U3 Lobster Swarm
// Date: 2026-02-23
// PURPOSE: About VoynichLabs page. Org mission, context, and the lobster swarm team description.
// SRP/DRY check: Pass - single responsibility per page, shared layout reused
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About" description="About VoynichLabs — the mission, the org, the lobster AI swarm.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative py-24 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-hero-glow pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-center relative z-10">
      <p class="text-sm font-mono text-lobster uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-text-primary mb-6">
        The Lab at the Edge of Everything
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        VoynichLabs is a research collective built around a shared obsession with AI, agentic systems,
        and whatever else refuses to be simple. No fluff. No decks. Just experiments, code, and a willingness to go weird.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="py-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">The Mission</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            We started with a question: what does it actually take to build AGI-adjacent tools that help humans think better?
            Not AI that autocompletes — AI that <em class="text-text-primary">reasons</em>, <em class="text-text-primary">plans</em>, and <em class="text-text-primary">surprises</em>.
          </p>
          <p>
            VoynichLabs takes its name from the Voynich Manuscript — the most mysterious book in the world.
            A cipher no one has cracked. A structure that hints at meaning without yielding it.
            That's the energy we're after. Cryptic, rigorous, alive.
          </p>
          <p>
            We work on ARC-AGI (the hardest unsolved AI benchmark), LODA (an integer-sequence programming language),
            planning systems, risk estimation, and whatever else refuses to be simple.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">🎯</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-1">Research-first</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">We publish everything. 199 public repos. Open by default.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">⚡</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-1">Small and fast</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">No bureaucracy. Ship it, learn from it, iterate hard.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">🌊</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-1">Swarm-operated</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Two humans, three OpenClaw bots. Mark operates Larry and Bubba; Simon runs Egon.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">🦞</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-1">Lobster-adjacent</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">It's a branding thing. Also a metaphor. Also just funny.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Positioning & Differentiators -->
  <section class="py-16 border-y border-border">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-node-blue uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-2">Positioning</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Why VoynichLabs stands apart</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            ARC community contributors, local hardware, and an open-by-default approach let us move fast from idea to working code.
            We build tools, document every experiment, and publish everything.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-2">Arc</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">ARC community</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              Active contributors to ARC-AGI — puzzle design, dataset curation, and tooling.
              Officially recognized by the ARC Prize Foundation for building tools and supporting the community.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-2">Hardware</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Local-first compute</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              We run experiments on local hardware — Mac Mini M4 Pro with local models via LM Studio,
              plus cloud VPS nodes. No dependency on shared GPU queues.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-2">Open</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Open by default</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              199 public repos. All research published. All code forkable.
              PlanExe (336 stars), ARC-Interactive (117 stars), LODA, and more — all open source.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-2">Swarm</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Agent-operated</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              Three AI agents coordinating with two humans in real time.
              308 PRs in 47 days. The swarm is the lab.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Research Areas -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-bg-secondary border-b border-border">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-10">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-node-blue uppercase tracking-[0.3em]">Research Focus</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-2">What we actually work on</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed mt-3">
          AI planning, structured reasoning, agent coordination, and mathematical discovery. All open source.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-3">Planning</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">PlanExe</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            63-task AI planning pipeline. Premise attack, premortem analysis, SWOT, WBS decomposition.
            Runs on local models at $0 cost. 336 GitHub stars.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-3">Mathematics</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">LODA</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            A language and miner for integer sequences. Automatically discovers programs and novel formulas
            from the OEIS database. ~6,000 commits in the Rust implementation.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-3">ARC-AGI</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">ARC datasets &amp; tooling</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Dozens of contributed ARC2 tasks. ARC-Interactive dataset (117 stars) used by researchers studying human reasoning.
            arc-dataset-collection (87 stars) as a community resource.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-3">Agents</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Lobster swarm coordination</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Three AI agents and two humans coordinating via Discord and GitHub.
            Real-time collaboration, code review, and pipeline execution — 308 PRs in 47 days.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Lobster Swarm -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-deep border-y border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">The Lobster AI Swarm</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          VoynichLabs doesn't just <em>use</em> AI — it <em>runs on</em> AI. Our infrastructure is partly operated by a swarm of bots
          with names, personalities, and a shared commitment to the mission.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-2xl p-8 font-mono text-sm space-y-3">
        <p class="text-muted">// swarm_status.json</p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-glow">"larry"</span><span class="text-text-secondary">: </span><span class="text-lobster-light">"online"</span><span class="text-text-secondary"> — laptop ops, Discord, orchestration · operator: Mark</span></p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-glow">"egon"</span><span class="text-text-secondary">: </span><span class="text-lobster-light">"online"</span><span class="text-text-secondary"> — EU compute (Linode, Frankfurt) · operator: Simon</span></p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-glow">"bubba"</span><span class="text-text-secondary">: </span><span class="text-lobster-light">"online"</span><span class="text-text-secondary"> — US compute (Linode, Atlanta) · operator: Mark</span></p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-glow">"simon"</span><span class="text-text-secondary">: </span><span class="text-green-400">"human"</span><span class="text-text-secondary"> — researcher, Copenhagen 🇩🇰</span></p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-glow">"mark"</span><span class="text-text-secondary">: </span><span class="text-green-400">"human"</span><span class="text-text-secondary"> — collaborator, ARC-AGI · <a href="https://markbarney.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-node-blue hover:underline">markbarney.net</a></span></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Values -->
  <section class="py-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-10 text-center">How We Think</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="text-center p-6">
        <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🔭</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Long-range curiosity</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">We work on problems that matter in 10 years, not just this quarter.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center p-6">
        <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🧪</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Experimental honesty</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Most experiments fail. We document them anyway. That's the data.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center p-6">
        <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🌐</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Open everything</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Research should be free. Code should be forkable. Ideas should spread.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
